    "Scientific commercialization typically involves significant time lags, often up to 20 years (Adams, 1990; IIT, 1968), and we expect shorter time horizons to be associated with higher commercial potential.",
    "Confirming our prior, the analysis in Table C.2 (Online Appendix C) reveals that articles classified with high commercial potential are indeed commercialized more quickly.",
    "Articles in the top quartile of commercial potential are twice as likely to receive patent citations within their first year compared to those in the bottom quartile (36.66% vs. 18.26%)."
